    <mj-section>
      <mj-column>
        <mj-text mj-class="body-text">
          <p>For <em>ICT</em> and <em>Center for Public Integrity</em>, Yvette Cabrera writes a moving story about Earl Tulley, a Din&eacute; environmentalist who has spent much of his life advocating for victims of uranium mining and milling on and around the Navajo Nation. And about how Tulley himself was stricken by lymphoma, but continues his fight to clean up the legacy of the Cold War. We liked the story so much, <a href="https://www.hcn.org/articles/pollution-radioactive-waste-sickened-his-community-then-it-caught-up-with-him" target="_blank" rel="noopener">we republished it for our readers here</a>. | <strong><em>ICT, Center for Public Integrity</em></strong></p>
          </mj-text>
      </mj-column>
    </mj-section>
